  "Title": "Asteroid Collision",
  "Description": "Given an array of integers representing asteroids in a row, find the state after all collisions.\n\nPositive = moving right, Negative = moving left. Same speed.\nSmaller asteroid explodes on collision. Equal size = both explode. Same direction = never collide.\n\nFirst line: N. Second line: N integers.\n\n**Example:**\n- Input:\n```\n3\n5 10 -5\n```\n- Output: `5 10`\n\n**Constraints:**\n- 2 <= N <= 10,000\n- -1000 <= asteroid <= 1000, asteroid != 0\n- Expected complexity: O(N)",
  "Difficulty": 2,
  "TimeLimitMs": 3000,
  "MemoryLimitKb": 65536,
